{"id":1002,"date":"2021-04-14T17:25:28","date_gmt":"2021-04-14T17:25:28","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/programming.sdarobotics.org\/?page_id=1002"},"modified":"2024-09-02T18:51:00","modified_gmt":"2024-09-02T18:51:00","slug":"assembling-the-chassis","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/assembling-the-chassis\/","title":{"rendered":"Assembling the Chassis"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>First attach the<strong>&nbsp;Drive Motor Mount<\/strong>&nbsp;to the&nbsp;<strong>Chassis<\/strong>&nbsp;with eight 3\/4 inch 8-32 bolts as shown below. Make sure that the large hole in the chassis is at the back of the robot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1926\" width=\"440\" height=\"398\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis1.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis1-300x272.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis1-150x136.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis1-768x695.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 440px) 100vw, 440px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now drill the three holes in the&nbsp;<strong>Swivel Wheel Mount<\/strong>&nbsp;as indicated below using a 3\/16 inch drill:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SwivelWheelMount-Drill.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SwivelWheelMount-Drill.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1010\" width=\"250\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SwivelWheelMount-Drill.jpg 503w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SwivelWheelMount-Drill-300x262.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/SwivelWheelMount-Drill-150x131.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 250px) 100vw, 250px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then attach the&nbsp;<strong>Swivel Wheel Mount<\/strong>&nbsp;together with the&nbsp;<strong>Circuit Breaker Mount<\/strong>&nbsp;using two 1-1\/2 inch 8-32 bolts as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2-1024x491.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1930\" width=\"533\" height=\"255\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2-1024x491.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2-300x144.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2-150x72.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2-768x368.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2-1536x736.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis2.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 533px) 100vw, 533px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Prepare the Gyro Mount by tapping the holes as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/GyroMount-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1941\" width=\"301\" height=\"269\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/GyroMount-1.jpg 605w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/GyroMount-1-300x268.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/GyroMount-1-150x134.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 301px) 100vw, 301px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the three&nbsp;<strong>Motor Controller Mounts<\/strong>, two on the top and one on the bottom, the two <strong>Power Distribution Mounts<\/strong> on the sides, the <strong>Raspberry Pi Mount<\/strong>, and the <strong>Gyro Mount<\/strong> using 8-32 bolts as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-1024x440.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1932\" width=\"499\" height=\"213\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-1024x440.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-300x129.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-150x64.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-768x330.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-1536x660.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis3-2048x880.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next, attach the two&nbsp;<strong>Power Distribution Modules<\/strong>&nbsp;using four 1\/2 inch 8-32 bolts. Place the red one on the left and the black one on the right as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis4.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1937\" width=\"402\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis4.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis4-300x246.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis4-150x123.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis4-768x629.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the two&nbsp;<strong>Drive Motors<\/strong>&nbsp;to the mount using three 1\/4 inch M3 screws. Be careful to&nbsp;<strong>not<\/strong>&nbsp;use longer screws as they can penetrate the gear casing far enough to interfere with the gears. Once you have attached the two drive motors, use zip ties to fasten the other end of the motors to the chassis as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis5.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1939\" width=\"426\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis5.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis5-300x247.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis5-150x123.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/Chassis5-768x632.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 426px) 100vw, 426px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next attach the&nbsp;<strong>Swivel Wheel<\/strong>&nbsp;to the back of the robot using four 1\/2 inch 8-32 bolts as shown below:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/SwivelWheel.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1943\" width=\"455\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/SwivelWheel.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/SwivelWheel-300x229.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/SwivelWheel-150x115.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/SwivelWheel-768x587.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 455px) 100vw, 455px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the&nbsp;<strong>wheels<\/strong>&nbsp;using two&nbsp;<strong>6mm bore hex couplers<\/strong>. Then use a 1\/4 inch M4 screw to attach the wheels to the hex couplers:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-1024x437.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1945\" width=\"595\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-1024x437.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-300x128.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-150x64.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-768x328.jpg 768w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-1536x656.jpg 1536w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/WheelMount-2048x874.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 595px) 100vw, 595px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Next we are going to attach the power wires that will connect to the battery. Cut a 16 inch piece of 16 gauge red and black wire. On one end, crimp&nbsp;<strong>U connectors<\/strong>&nbsp;that will screw into the power distribution module. On the other end connect the proper connector for the battery you have chosen. (In my case these are&nbsp;<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https:\/\/www.amazon.com\/gp\/product\/B081MQNGR1\/ref=ppx_yo_dt_b_asin_title_o00_s00?ie=UTF8&amp;psc=1\" target=\"_blank\">XT60 connectors<\/a>):<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-large is-resized\"><a href=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PowerWire.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PowerWire.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1053\" width=\"379\" height=\"343\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PowerWire.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PowerWire-300x272.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PowerWire-150x136.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/04\/PowerWire-768x698.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 379px) 100vw, 379px\" \/><\/a><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Then feed the wire from the top through the large hole and connect the red and black wires the their respective power distribution modules:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerBottom.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1948\" width=\"440\" height=\"348\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerBottom.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerBottom-300x238.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerBottom-150x119.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerBottom-768x608.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 440px) 100vw, 440px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>Now attach the&nbsp;<strong>Circuit Breaker<\/strong>&nbsp;to the&nbsp;<strong>Circuit Breaker Mount <\/strong>on the back of the robot. Then cut the red power wire on the top and feed each end into either side of the&nbsp;<strong>Circuit Breaker<\/strong>&nbsp;as shown:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter size-full is-resized\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerTop.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-1950\" width=\"437\" height=\"377\" srcset=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerTop.jpg 1024w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerTop-300x259.jpg 300w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerTop-150x129.jpg 150w, http:\/\/gabybot.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/MainPowerTop-768x662.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 437px) 100vw, 437px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n\n<p>We will now&nbsp;mount&nbsp;the first of 3&nbsp;<strong>Step Up Regulators<\/strong>. Note that if you are using a 12v battery, this first regulator is not needed. In that case you should connect the battery directly to the motor controller.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"\/assembling-the-turret\/\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"\/assembling-the-turret\/\">Next: Assembling the Turret<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>First attach the&nbsp;Drive Motor Mount&nbsp;to the&nbsp;Chassis&nbsp;with eight 3\/4 inch 8-32 bolts as shown below. Make sure that the large hole in the chassis is at the back of the robot. Now drill the three holes in the&nbsp;Swivel Wheel Mount&nbsp;as indi